009	1SA	001	001	There was a man called Elkanah. He was from Ephraim’s tribe, and he lived in a town called Ramah in the hill country. His father was Jeroham, his grand-father was Elihu, and his great grand-father was Tohu. He belonged to the Zuf family.
009	1SA	001	002	He had 2 wives called Hannah and Penninah. Penninah had some kids, but Hannah had none.
