043	JOH	001	019	The Jewish leaders in Jerusalem city sent some of the bosses of their ceremonies, and other men that helped in the Jewish ceremonies, to ask John some questions. They said to him, “Who are you?”
043	JOH	001	020	John told them straight. He said, “I am not the Christ, the special man that God promised to send to save his people.”
043	JOH	001	021	Those men from Jerusalem asked him again, “Who are you then? Are you Elijah, the man that told God’s message a long time ago?” John said, “No, I am not Elijah.” Again, the men asked, “What about the messenger that God promised, a long time ago. He promised to send a special man, like Moses, to tell his message. Are you that man?” And again, John said, “No, I am not that man.”
043	JOH	001	022	Then the men asked him, “Well, who are you? And why are you here? We have to tell our leaders.”
