# BOOK	045	ROM	Romans	Romans
045	ROM	001	001	I am Paul, and this letter is from me. I work for Jesus Christ, and God picked me to be Jesus’s special worker, to go and tell people the good news that he will save them.
045	ROM	001	002	A long time ago, God promised to do that. He got some of his men to tell people about it, and they wrote about it in God’s book.
045	ROM	001	003	That good news is about our leader Jesus Christ. He was born into David’s family. David was the big boss of the Jewish nation a long time ago. Jesus was born as a human being into David’s family, but really, Jesus is God’s own son. God showed us in a powerful way that Jesus is his son. He did it like this. People killed Jesus, but God used his Holy Spirit to make him alive again.
045	ROM	001	005	And you know, God is very good to me. He picked me to be Jesus’s special worker. He told me to go to people that are not Jews to tell them about Jesus, and get them to believe in him and do whatever he says.
045	ROM	001	006	And God wanted you to believe in him and to do what he says too. God picked you, so now you belong to Jesus Christ.
045	ROM	001	007	I’m sending this letter to all you people that belong to God, and that live in the city called Rome. God picked you to follow him, and to be his people. I’m asking God our father, and Jesus Christ our leader, to be good to you, and to make you feel happy and quiet inside yourselves.
045	ROM	001	008	The first thing I want to do is to say thank you to my God. I can talk to God and say thank you because Jesus Christ made us God’s friends. I thank God for all of you Christian mob there. You really believe in Jesus now, and people everywhere in the world are talking about how you really trust in Jesus.
045	ROM	001	009	I pray to God all the time, and I ask him to help you. That’s true. God knows it’s true. I work hard for God, I tell everyone the good news about his son.
045	ROM	001	010	Whenever I pray to him, I ask him that, if he agrees, he will let me come and see you soon.
045	ROM	001	011	I have been waiting for a long time. I really want to see you. I want to help you get more power from God to make you strong.
045	ROM	001	012	Then I will see how much you trust God and you will see how much I trust God, and that will make all of us happy.
045	ROM	001	013	You know, friends, I tried to come and see you lots of times, but God stopped me every time. I want to come and work there with you and get more people to follow Jesus, just like I do at other places.
045	ROM	001	014	I’ve got to tell God’s word to all sorts of people. I have to tell it to people that have my culture, and to people that have other cultures. I have to tell it to people that can think good and to people that can’t think good. I have to tell everybody God’s word.
045	ROM	001	015	So I want to come to Rome and tell God’s good news to all you mob there too.
045	ROM	001	016	I don’t feel any shame about God’s good news. It is a really good story because it has God’s power in it. Whenever people believe this good news, God saves them. It is the same for everybody, for Jewish people and for people that are not Jews.
045	ROM	001	017	God’s good news is this. God saves people that trust him, and he makes them properly good. God says this in his book, “If you trust God, he will say you are good, and you will really live.”
045	ROM	001	018	God in heaven gets very angry with people that do bad things. He gets angry whenever they do things against him, and whenever they do bad things to other people. They go against God, but that’s not all, they try to stop other people hearing the true story about God. And that makes God very angry.
045	ROM	001	019	God clearly shows everybody enough for us to understand the true story about him. Everybody knows about him.
045	ROM	001	020	Even though we can’t see God, we can know about him. If we look at the things he has made, we can know about him, that he is really great and really strong. Ever since he made the world, we can look at everything that he made, and we can know about him from those things. So nobody can say that they don’t know about God. (aïdios g126)
045	ROM	001	021	The trouble was this. Even though people could work that out about God, they really didn’t want to know him. They didn’t want to say to him, “Thank you, you really are the true God.” They couldn’t think properly about him. They could only think in stupid ways. They didn’t understand anything.
045	ROM	001	022	They told everybody that they could think really good, but they were fools.
045	ROM	001	023	They didn’t respect the wonderful God that never dies, but instead they made models of things that do die. They made things that look like people, or birds, or animals, or snakes, or those sorts of things, and they respected those things. They didn’t respect God.
045	ROM	001	024	So God let them go their own way, and they did whatever they felt like doing. They did whatever their dirty minds thought about, so they did bad things with each other’s bodies.
045	ROM	001	025	They didn’t want the true story about God. They wanted to believe a lie, and they respected the things that God made instead of respecting God himself. You know, God is really great, and everyone has to tell him, “You are really good.” And they have to keep on doing it for ever. Yes, that’s right, but people didn’t respect God like that. (aiōn g165)
